emotions of another person?

00:09:09.350 --> 00:09:12.500 align:middle line:84%
Can our emotions
actually influence

00:09:12.500 --> 00:09:14.636 align:middle line:90%
the DNA in our bodies?

00:09:14.636 --> 00:09:16.010 align:middle line:84%
Before I tell you
the experiment,

00:09:16.010 --> 00:09:20.030 align:middle line:84%
let me just share a little bit
about why this is important.

00:09:20.030 --> 00:09:23.930 align:middle line:84%
Human DNA, when it
is in our cells,

00:09:23.930 --> 00:09:27.890 align:middle line:84%
it is coiled in very
specific kinds of ways.

00:09:27.890 --> 00:09:30.380 align:middle line:84%
And what scientists
have found is

00:09:30.380 --> 00:09:33.680 align:middle line:84%
that in the presence
of certain emotions

00:09:33.680 --> 00:09:36.020 align:middle line:84%
that we would call
negative emotions--

00:09:36.020 --> 00:09:38.310 align:middle line:84%
and I don't really
like to use that term,

00:09:38.310 --> 00:09:41.210 align:middle line:84%
but I'm going to use it to be
clear what we're talking about.

00:09:41.210 --> 00:09:44.720 align:middle line:84%
So when we talk about
emotions, for example,

00:09:44.720 --> 00:09:49.220 align:middle line:84%
of anger or hate or jealousy
or rage or frustration, those

00:09:49.220 --> 00:09:52.470 align:middle line:84%
that we would typically
consider as negative emotions,

00:09:52.470 --> 00:09:56.140 align:middle line:84%
they have an effect on
the DNA within our bodies.

00:09:56.140 --> 00:10:00.230 align:middle line:84%
And the effect is that in the
presence of those emotions,

00:10:00.230 --> 00:10:03.170 align:middle line:84%
the DNA is actually--
coil is tightened.

00:10:03.170 --> 00:10:05.510 align:middle line:84%
It's tightened
like a little knot.

00:10:05.510 --> 00:10:07.760 align:middle line:84%
And that's important,
because when

00:10:07.760 --> 00:10:12.020 align:middle line:84%
it is tightened in this way,
the DNA does not express

00:10:12.020 --> 00:10:14.180 align:middle line:90%
to its fullest capacity.

00:10:14.180 --> 00:10:17.810 align:middle line:84%
So negative emotions
tighten the coil

00:10:17.810 --> 00:10:20.600 align:middle line:84%
and prevent the
DNA from expressing

00:10:20.600 --> 00:10:23.300 align:middle line:84%
the fullest capacity of whatever
it is that it is expressing.

00:10:23.300 --> 00:10:26.930 align:middle line:84%
Whether it's our immune response
or our anti-aging hormones

00:10:26.930 --> 00:10:31.220 align:middle line:84%
or whatever it is, the DNA
simply cannot do its full

00:10:31.220 --> 00:10:33.890 align:middle line:84%
complement of what
it's designed to do.

00:10:33.890 --> 00:10:35.780 align:middle line:84%
So from this description,
you can probably

00:10:35.780 --> 00:10:38.210 align:middle line:84%
imagine what the
positive emotions do.

00:10:38.210 --> 00:10:42.190 align:middle line:84%
Positive emotions
actually loosen the DNA.

00:10:42.190 --> 00:10:44.660 align:middle line:90%
They relax the DNA.

00:10:44.660 --> 00:10:50.150 align:middle line:84%
So these are the emotions
of compassion, gratitude,

00:10:50.150 --> 00:10:51.980 align:middle line:90%
appreciation, for example.

00:10:51.980 --> 00:10:57.410 align:middle line:84%
Those kinds of emotions actually
relax the DNA within our bodies

00:10:57.410 --> 00:11:00.290 align:middle line:84%
and allow that
fullest expression.

00:11:00.290 --> 00:11:02.810 align:middle line:84%
Knowing this, the
scientists wanted

00:11:02.810 --> 00:11:07.520 align:middle line:84%
to see what effect human
emotion from one person

00:11:07.520 --> 00:11:12.120 align:middle line:84%
would have upon DNA that's
not in that person's body,

00:11:12.120 --> 00:11:14.360 align:middle line:84%
but it's in this special
container that was designed.

00:11:14.360 --> 00:11:16.370 align:middle line:90%
So that's the experiment.

00:11:16.370 --> 00:11:17.720 align:middle line:90%
Here's what they found.

00:11:17.720 --> 00:11:20.150 align:middle line:90%
The human DNA was isolated.

00:11:20.150 --> 00:11:24.032 align:middle line:10%
And in the presence of
the positive emotions,

00:11:24.032 --> 00:11:26.240 align:middle line:10%
in the presence of the
gratitude, appreciation, love,

00:11:26.240 --> 00:11:28.640 align:middle line:10%
and compassion,
