00:16:45.040 --> 00:16:48.190 align:middle line:84%
They're called Newtonian
physics, classical physics.

00:16:48.190 --> 00:16:50.410 align:middle line:84%
It was all about
things bumping up

00:16:50.410 --> 00:16:55.840 align:middle line:84%
against other things, electrons
and atoms and neutrons.

00:16:55.840 --> 00:16:58.334 align:middle line:84%
But the new physics that
was developing at the time

00:16:58.334 --> 00:17:00.250 align:middle line:84%
through the theories
that were being developed

00:17:00.250 --> 00:17:03.220 align:middle line:84%
in the late 1800s
and early 1900s,

00:17:03.220 --> 00:17:05.770 align:middle line:84%
that physics said that
there's something else that's

00:17:05.770 --> 00:17:08.560 align:middle line:84%
happening that on the level
of things that are very small

00:17:08.560 --> 00:17:13.390 align:middle line:84%
and the level of things that are
